<body>

  
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🍛 Naan with Butter Chicken</h1>
       

        <h2>Ingredients for Naan:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups All-Purpose Flour</li>
            <li>½ tsp Baking Soda</li>
            <li>¼ cup Yogurt</li>
            <li>½ cup Milk</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Oil</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Butter for brushing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Ingredients for Butter Chicken:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>500g Chicken (Boneless, Cut into Pieces)</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Butter</li>
            <li>1 Onion (Finely Chopped)</li>
            <li>2 Tomatoes (Pureed)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
            <li>½ cup Fresh Cream</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Kasuri Methi (Dried Fenugreek Leaves)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>**For Naan:** Mix all ingredients, knead dough, let it rest for 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Roll the dough into oval shapes and cook on a hot pan until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Brush with butter and serve warm.</li>
            <li>**For Butter Chicken:** Heat butter, sauté onions, and add ginger-garlic paste.</li>
            <li>Add tomato puree, spices, and cook until thick.</li>
            <li>Add chicken and simmer for 15 minutes.</li>
            <li>Stir in cream and Kasuri methi, cook for 5 more minutes.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with naan.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
